os â†’ Standard library module
     Used to interact with the operating system.
     Examples: file/dir ops, env vars, system commands
     ðŸ‘‰ os.system(), os.getenv(), os.makedirs()

sys â†’ Standard library module
      Used to interact with Python runtime.
      Examples: CLI args, exit, path
      ðŸ‘‰ sys.argv, sys.exit(), sys.path

shutil â†’ Standard library module
         Used for high-level file , directory operations.
         Examples: copy, move, delete directories/files
         ðŸ‘‰ shutil.copy(), shutil.copytree() , shutil.disk_usage(path)

boto3 â†’ External library (AWS SDK for Python)
        Used to manage AWS services programmatically.
        Examples: EC2, S3, IAM, RDS
        ðŸ‘‰ boto3.client('s3'), boto3.resource('ec2')
        
psutil â†’ External library
         Used for system monitoring.
         Examples: CPU, memory, disk, process info
        ðŸ‘‰ psutil.cpu_percent(), psutil.virtual_memory()
		

