Q) How can I create a multiline string in Python?

Answer:

    - You can create a multiline string using triple quotes:
        - '''  (triple single quotes)
        - """  (triple double quotes)

    Example:

        s = '''This is a
        multiline string'''

        print(s)

    - Python will preserve the line breaks exactly as written.


